<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/10–1044: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-10T17:00:00-04:00">October 10,
                                1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1316. For Friedman from Treasury.</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Treasury would appreciate (reference your 1383, August 10, 1944<note n="16" xml:id="d693fn16">Not printed.</note>) <list>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Details on any recent criticisms of the Central Bank’s gold
                                    selling policy in the press and at the last People’s Political
                                    Council meeting.</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Details on the spread between forward and spot and who
                                    specifically benefitted from it.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>A speedy reply is desired. [Morgenthau.]</item>
                    </list>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>